<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="297" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Norwegian Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Norway</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-05-05"><hi rend="italic">May 5,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform your excellency
                            that His Majesty King Haakon has decided that the coronation shall take
                            place June 22 next.</p>
                        <p>Accept, sir, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Chr. Hauge.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>